  "commentary": "With SPX at 6607.94 sitting right at the GEX flip (6607) and just above the massive +13.3B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to sell any further upside moves as their long gamma positioning kicks in. The PIN regime confirms stabilizing forces are in play, with dealers acting as shock absorbers by selling rallies and buying dips around current levels. Key levels to watch are the 6605 max positive gamma strike as immediate support and the 6610 resistance level with +10.8B in stabilizing gamma.\n\nThe recent wall_break event combined with the -13% 1-minute decline suggests we're seeing the gamma stabilization mechanism actively working, with dealer buying likely providing a floor near the 6605 strike.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned near 6605-6610 with limited big moves in either direction.",
